tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting significant renal dysfunction, possibly acute or chronic kidney disease with impaired concentrating ability. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may indicate underlying infection or tubular injury, though no leukocytes or nitrites are detected. Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, so diabetes is unlikely. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further workup for renal pathology.
